<%# Phase 29 (settings refactor) ‚Äî row 3 stack pane.

    FB-51 (2026-05-20) ‚Äî restructured from a 3x2 tile grid into a
    VERTICAL stack of 6 sub-panels per user-locked order. The stack
    pane now lives in the 40% right column of the FB-52 V3 layout, so
    a vertical sub-panel arrangement fits the narrower width.

    Sub-panel order (top-to-bottom, user-locked 2026-05-20):

      ‚îå‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îê
      ‚îÇ Redis        [connected] ‚îÇ
      ‚îÇ   <sidekiq counters>     ‚îÇ
      ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î§
      ‚îÇ PostgreSQL   [connected] ‚îÇ
      ‚îÇ   <breakdown table>      ‚îÇ
      ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î§
      ‚îÇ Meilisearch  [connected] ‚îÇ
      ‚îÇ   <breakdown table>      ‚îÇ
      ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î§
      ‚îÇ Voyage AI    [configured]‚îÇ
      ‚îÇ   <voyage stats>         ‚îÇ
      ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î§
      ‚îÇ assets       [writable]  ‚îÇ
      ‚îÇ   <breakdown table>      ‚îÇ
      ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î§
      ‚îÇ notes        [absent]    ‚îÇ
      ‚îÇ   <breakdown table>      ‚îÇ
      ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îò

    Per-tile inline border-right / border-bottom dropped (the 2-col
    tile divider lines from the prior 3x2 grid). The vertical
    `gap: 8px` between flex children separates sub-panels cleanly;
    no hairlines needed between them.

    FB-68 (2026-05-20, folded into FB-51) ‚Äî zebra background removed
    from `.tui-table--stack` rows. The dashed hairline body row from
    the canonical `.tui-table` grammar is the row separator; no
    zebra anywhere in stack-pane tables.

    Status chips remain per sub-panel: each sub-panel header looks up
    its semantic state in `Settings::Stack::HealthState::STATES` and
    renders the resolved chip label + variant via `Tui::ChipComponent`.
    The chip variant cascade (success / danger after FB-6) carries the
    operator signal.

    Reuses the same ivars + helpers the prior settings index relied
    on (`@postgres_status`, `@redis_status`,
    `@search_per_index_stats`, `@postgres_table_breakdown`,
    `@sidekiq_breakdown`, `@storage_status`, `@notes_volume_status`,
    `@assets_breakdown`, `@notes_breakdown`, `@voyage_configured`,
    `@search_healthy`).

    `data-controller="stack-stats-live"` mounts the polling controller
    (`app/javascript/controllers/stack_stats_live_controller.js`). It
    hits `GET /settings/stack_stats` every 3 s and patches cells with
    `data-stack-stats-live-target` in place. Connection-health probes,
    table sizes, and per-index docs stay on the server-side render ‚Äî
    they flip rarely and are expensive to recompute. Polling stops on
    Turbo navigation away (Stimulus `disconnect()` clears the
    interval). %>
<div class="pane pane--wide pito-pane pito-pane--full"
     data-controller="stack-stats-live"
     data-stack-stats-live-interval-ms-value="3000"
     data-tui-cursor-target="panel"
     data-panel-title="<%= t("settings.stack.heading") %>">
  <span class="pito-pane__title"><%= t("settings.stack.heading") %></span>
  <%= render Tui::PanelFieldsetComponent.new do %>
    <%# FB-51 ‚Äî vertical sub-panel stack. The `.stack-pane-grid`
        container still wraps the children (CSS now flexes the
        container vertically with an 8px gap between sub-panels). %>
    <div class="stack-pane-grid">

      <%# Redis (+ Sidekiq counters since Sidekiq runs on Redis).
          FB-63-V4 ‚Äî V4 title-in-border chrome: title left, status chip
          right. The legacy sub-panel header row is gone; the chip
          moves into `.pito-sub-panel__actions`. State ‚Üí chip label +
          variant resolution lives in
          `Settings::Stack::HealthState::STATES` (FB-82). %>
      <% redis_state = @redis_status[:connected] ? :connected : :disconnected %>
      <% redis_chip = Settings::Stack::HealthState::STATES.fetch(redis_state) %>
      <%= render Tui::SubPanelComponent.new(title: t("settings.stack.redis")) do |c| %>
        <% c.with_actions do %>
          <%= render Tui::ChipComponent.new(label: redis_chip[:chip_label], variant: redis_chip[:chip_variant]) %>
        <% end %>

        <% if @redis_status[:connected] && @sidekiq_breakdown.any? %>
          <%= render Settings::Stack::Sidekiq::CountersComponent.new(breakdown: @sidekiq_breakdown) %>
        <% end %>
      <% end %>

      <%# PostgreSQL. FB-63-V4 ‚Äî V4 title-in-border. %>
      <% pg_state = @postgres_status[:connected] ? :connected : :disconnected %>
      <% pg_chip = Settings::Stack::HealthState::STATES.fetch(pg_state) %>
      <%= render Tui::SubPanelComponent.new(title: t("settings.stack.postgres")) do |c| %>
        <% c.with_actions do %>
          <%= render Tui::ChipComponent.new(label: pg_chip[:chip_label], variant: pg_chip[:chip_variant]) %>
        <% end %>

        <% if @postgres_status[:connected] && @postgres_table_breakdown.any? %>
          <div data-controller="sortable-table" data-sortable-table-id-value="stack-postgres">
            <table class="tui-table tui-table--stack" data-sortable-table-target="table">
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <%= render(SortableHeaderComponent.new(label: t("settings.stack.col_model"), sort_type: "string")) %>
                  <%= render(SortableHeaderComponent.new(label: t("settings.stack.col_rows"), sort_type: "number", numeric: true)) %>
                  <%= render(SortableHeaderComponent.new(label: t("settings.stack.col_size"), sort_type: "number", numeric: true)) %>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <%# Every Postgres row carries
                    `data-stack-stats-live-target="postgres<Label><Field>"`
                    so the polling controller can patch the rows + size
                    cells in place every ~3 s without a full-page reload. %>
                <% @postgres_table_breakdown.each do |row| %>
                  <% key = row[:label].to_s.camelize %>
                  <tr class="tui-table__row">
                    <td class="tui-table__td"><%= row[:label] %></td>
                    <td class="tui-table__td tui-table__td--right num">
                      <span data-sort-value="<%= row[:count] || -1 %>"
                            data-stack-stats-live-target="postgres<%= key %>Rows">
                        <%= row[:count] ? number_with_delimiter(row[:count]) : "‚Äî" %>
                      </span>
                    </td>
                    <td class="tui-table__td tui-table__td--right num">
                      <span data-sort-value="<%= row[:size_bytes] || -1 %>"
                            data-stack-stats-live-target="postgres<%= key %>Size">
                        <%= human_filesize_int(row[:size_bytes]) %>
                      </span>
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                <% end %>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
        <% end %>
      <% end %>

      <%# Meilisearch.
          FB-126 (2026-05-21) ‚Äî `[reindex]` now opens a
          `Tui::ConfirmationDialogComponent` instead of POSTing directly;
          the dialog (mounted at the bottom of the panel) carries the
          actual form to `settings_stack_meilisearch_reindex_path`.
          On submit, the job emits a `reindex_started` cable event
          (brand: `meilisearch`) and the `reindex-action` Stimulus
          controller below swaps `[reindex]` for the
          `Tui::ReindexProgressComponent` `[=------]` indicator in
          place. When the job's `ensure` block re-broadcasts via
          `StackStats::Broadcaster.broadcast!` with `reindex.running:
          false`, the indicator flips back to `[reindex]`.

          The idle + running children sit in the same DOM, toggled via
          `hidden` so the action slot never collapses (no width jitter
          when the swap fires). %>
      <% meilisearch_reindex_running = AppSetting.reindex_running? %>
      <% meili_state = @search_healthy ? :connected : :disconnected %>
      <% meili_chip = Settings::Stack::HealthState::STATES.fetch(meili_state) %>
      <%= render Tui::SubPanelComponent.new(title: t("settings.stack.meilisearch")) do |c| %>
        <% c.with_actions do %>
          <%= render Tui::ChipComponent.new(label: meili_chip[:chip_label], variant: meili_chip[:chip_variant]) %>
          <span data-controller="reindex-action"
                data-reindex-action-brand-value="meilisearch">
            <span data-reindex-action-target="idle" <%= "hidden" if meilisearch_reindex_running %>>
              <button type="button"
                      class="bracketed"
                      data-controller="reindex-trigger"
                      data-reindex-trigger-dialog-id-value="reindex_meilisearch_confirmation"
                      data-action="click->reindex-trigger#open">[<span class="bl"><%= t("settings.stack.meilisearch_reindex_label") %></span>]</button>
            </span>
            <span data-reindex-action-target="running" <%= "hidden" unless meilisearch_reindex_running %>>
              <%= render Tui::ReindexProgressComponent.new(brand: "meilisearch") %>
            </span>
          </span>
        <% end %>

        <% if @search_per_index_stats.any? %>
          <div data-controller="sortable-table" data-sortable-table-id-value="stack-meilisearch">
            <table class="tui-table tui-table--stack" data-sortable-table-target="table">
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <%= render(SortableHeaderComponent.new(label: t("settings.stack.col_index"), sort_type: "string")) %>
                  <%= render(SortableHeaderComponent.new(label: t("settings.stack.col_docs"), sort_type: "number", numeric: true)) %>
                  <%= render(SortableHeaderComponent.new(label: t("settings.stack.col_size"), sort_type: "number", numeric: true)) %>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <%# The unified `games_<env>` Meilisearch index is split
                    into two rows by `kind` (`game` / `bundle`). Size is
                    reported by Meilisearch at the INDEX level only;
                    `omit_size` rows render a plain dash in the size
                    column (the size is already attributed to the
                    `games` row, so duplicating it on `bundles` would
                    mislead the operator). %>
                <% @search_per_index_stats.each do |row| %>
                  <% key = row[:label].to_s.camelize %>
                  <tr class="tui-table__row">
                    <td class="tui-table__td"><%= row[:label] %></td>
                    <% if row[:missing] %>
                      <td class="tui-table__td tui-table__td--right num text-muted" colspan="2">
                        <span data-sort-value="-1"><%= t("settings.stack.not_yet_indexed") %></span>
                      </td>
                    <% else %>
                      <td class="tui-table__td tui-table__td--right num">
                        <span data-sort-value="<%= row[:documents].to_i %>"
                              data-stack-stats-live-target="meilisearch<%= key %>Docs">
                          <%= number_with_delimiter(row[:documents].to_i) %>
                        </span>
                      </td>
                      <% if row[:omit_size] %>
                        <td class="tui-table__td tui-table__td--right num text-muted">
                          <span data-sort-value="-1">‚Äî</span>
                        </td>
                      <% else %>
                        <td class="tui-table__td tui-table__td--right num">
                          <span data-sort-value="<%= row[:size_bytes] || -1 %>"
                                data-stack-stats-live-target="meilisearch<%= key %>Size">
                            <%= human_filesize_int(row[:size_bytes]) %>
                          </span>
                        </td>
                      <% end %>
                    <% end %>
                  </tr>
                <% end %>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
        <% end %>
      <% end %>

      <%# Voyage AI (+ stats table + title-row reindex action).
          Phase 32 follow-up ‚Äî Voyage section kept as a partial so the
          Voyage reindex job can Turbo-Stream-replace its
          `<div id="voyage_section">` without re-rendering the entire
          stack pane. The subscription below mounts the `reindex_status`
          stream; both `MeilisearchReindexJob` and `VoyageReindexJob`
          broadcast to it from their `ensure` blocks when the reindex
          completes (or crashes).

          FB-63-V4 (2026-05-20) ‚Äî Voyage sub-panel adopts V4
          title-in-border chrome. The wrapping `.pito-sub-panel`
          surrounds `<div id="voyage_section">` so the Turbo Stream
          replace inside the partial keeps repainting only the stats
          + running-state block; the V4 chrome (title left, chip +
          `[reindex]` right) lives in the parent here and stays put. %>
      <% voyage_state = AppSetting.voyage_configured? ? :configured : :not_configured %>
      <% voyage_chip = Settings::Stack::HealthState::STATES.fetch(voyage_state) %>
      <% voyage_reindex_running = AppSetting.reindex_running? %>
      <%= render Tui::SubPanelComponent.new(title: t("settings.voyage.heading")) do |c| %>
        <% c.with_actions do %>
          <%= render Tui::ChipComponent.new(label: voyage_chip[:chip_label], variant: voyage_chip[:chip_variant]) %>
          <%# FB-126 (2026-05-21) ‚Äî confirmation dialog + cable-driven
              idle/running toggle. Mirrors the Meilisearch sub-panel
              above; see the comment block on that branch for the full
              wire contract. %>
          <span data-controller="reindex-action"
                data-reindex-action-brand-value="voyage">
            <span data-reindex-action-target="idle" <%= "hidden" if voyage_reindex_running %>>
              <button type="button"
                      class="bracketed"
                      data-controller="reindex-trigger"
                      data-reindex-trigger-dialog-id-value="reindex_voyage_confirmation"
                      data-action="click->reindex-trigger#open">[<span class="bl"><%= t("settings.stack.voyage_reindex_label") %></span>]</button>
            </span>
            <span data-reindex-action-target="running" <%= "hidden" unless voyage_reindex_running %>>
              <%= render Tui::ReindexProgressComponent.new(brand: "voyage") %>
            </span>
          </span>
        <% end %>
        <%= turbo_stream_from "reindex_status" %>
        <%= render "voyage_section" %>
      <% end %>

      <%# assets. FB-63-V4 ‚Äî V4 title-in-border. %>
      <% assets_state = if @storage_status[:present]
                          @storage_status[:writable] ? :writable : :read_only
                        else
                          :absent
                        end %>
      <% assets_chip = Settings::Stack::HealthState::STATES.fetch(assets_state) %>
      <%= render Tui::SubPanelComponent.new(title: t("settings.stack.assets")) do |c| %>
        <% c.with_actions do %>
          <%= render Tui::ChipComponent.new(label: assets_chip[:chip_label], variant: assets_chip[:chip_variant]) %>
        <% end %>

        <% if @assets_breakdown.any? %>
          <div data-controller="sortable-table" data-sortable-table-id-value="stack-assets">
            <table class="tui-table tui-table--stack tui-table--3col-aligned" data-sortable-table-target="table">
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <%= render(SortableHeaderComponent.new(label: t("settings.stack.col_category"), sort_type: "string")) %>
                  <%= render(SortableHeaderComponent.new(label: t("settings.stack.col_files"), sort_type: "number", numeric: true)) %>
                  <%= render(SortableHeaderComponent.new(label: t("settings.stack.col_size"), sort_type: "number", numeric: true)) %>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <%# Assets rows expose live-stats targets so the polling
                    controller can patch file count + size in place. The
                    label-to-target mapping snake_cases the multi-word
                    "cover arts" label so it maps cleanly to a camelCase
                    Stimulus target name. %>
                <% @assets_breakdown.each do |row| %>
                  <% key = row[:label].to_s.tr(" ", "_").camelize %>
                  <tr class="tui-table__row">
                    <td class="tui-table__td"><%= row[:label] %></td>
                    <td class="tui-table__td tui-table__td--right num">
                      <span data-sort-value="<%= row[:file_count] || -1 %>"
                            data-stack-stats-live-target="assets<%= key %>Files">
                        <%= row[:file_count] ? number_with_delimiter(row[:file_count]) : "‚Äî" %>
                      </span>
                    </td>
                    <td class="tui-table__td tui-table__td--right num">
                      <span data-sort-value="<%= row[:size_bytes] || -1 %>"
                            data-stack-stats-live-target="assets<%= key %>Size">
                        <%= human_filesize_int(row[:size_bytes]) %>
                      </span>
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                <% end %>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
        <% end %>
      <% end %>

      <%# notes. FB-63-V4 ‚Äî V4 title-in-border. %>
      <% notes_state = if @notes_volume_status[:present]
                         @notes_volume_status[:writable] ? :writable : :read_only
                       else
                         :absent
                       end %>
      <% notes_chip = Settings::Stack::HealthState::STATES.fetch(notes_state) %>
      <%= render Tui::SubPanelComponent.new(title: t("settings.stack.notes")) do |c| %>
        <% c.with_actions do %>
          <%= render Tui::ChipComponent.new(label: notes_chip[:chip_label], variant: notes_chip[:chip_variant]) %>
        <% end %>

        <% if @notes_breakdown.any? %>
          <div data-controller="sortable-table" data-sortable-table-id-value="stack-notes">
            <table class="tui-table tui-table--stack tui-table--3col-aligned" data-sortable-table-target="table">
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <%= render(SortableHeaderComponent.new(label: t("settings.stack.col_namespace"), sort_type: "string")) %>
                  <%= render(SortableHeaderComponent.new(label: t("settings.stack.col_count"), sort_type: "number", numeric: true)) %>
                  <%= render(SortableHeaderComponent.new(label: t("settings.stack.col_size"), sort_type: "number", numeric: true)) %>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <% @notes_breakdown.each do |row| %>
                  <tr class="tui-table__row">
                    <td class="tui-table__td"><%= row[:label] %></td>
                    <td class="tui-table__td tui-table__td--right num">
                      <span data-sort-value="<%= row[:count] || -1 %>">
                        <%= row[:count] ? number_with_delimiter(row[:count]) : "‚Äî" %>
                      </span>
                    </td>
                    <td class="tui-table__td tui-table__td--right num">
                      <span data-sort-value="<%= row[:size_bytes] || -1 %>">
                        <%= human_filesize_int(row[:size_bytes]) %>
                      </span>
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                <% end %>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
        <% end %>
      <% end %>
    </div>
  <% end %>
  <%# FB-126 (2026-05-21) ‚Äî confirmation dialog mounts for each reindex
      sub-panel. Kept at the bottom of the pane (outside the sub-panel
      stack) so `<dialog>` is a sibling of the click trigger; the
      `Tui::ConfirmationDialogComponent` carries the actual POST form
      with `data-turbo: false` so the redirect-back flow stays intact.
      Both dialogs share the canonical danger styling on the confirm
      action. %>
  <%= render Tui::ConfirmationDialogComponent.new(
    id: "reindex_meilisearch_confirmation",
    title: t("settings.stack.meilisearch_reindex_confirm_title"),
    message: t("settings.stack.meilisearch_reindex_confirm_message"),
    action_label: t("settings.stack.meilisearch_reindex_label"),
    action_path: settings_stack_meilisearch_reindex_path,
    action_method: :post,
    action_variant: :danger
  ) %>
  <%= render Tui::ConfirmationDialogComponent.new(
    id: "reindex_voyage_confirmation",
    title: t("settings.stack.voyage_reindex_confirm_title"),
    message: t("settings.stack.voyage_reindex_confirm_message"),
    action_label: t("settings.stack.voyage_reindex_label"),
    action_path: settings_stack_voyage_reindex_path,
    action_method: :post,
    action_variant: :danger
  ) %>
</div>
